Package: qemu-system-zerotier
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: qemu-utils
Description: QEMU system emulator with ZeroTier network backend support
 QEMU is a generic machine emulator and virtualizer. This package contains
 the system emulator binaries with ZeroTier network backend support.
 .
 The ZeroTier network backend allows VMs to join ZeroTier virtual networks
 directly without requiring ZeroTier to be installed on the host system.
 Features:
  * Direct Layer 2 Ethernet integration with ZeroTier networks
  * Event-driven packet processing for high performance (800+ Mbps throughput)
  * Persistent ZeroTier identity and network credentials
  * Automatic MAC address assignment from ZeroTier
  * Low latency (1-7ms typical)

Package: qemu-zerotier-utils
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: QEMU ZeroTier utilities
 Utilities for the QEMU ZeroTier network backend, including configuration
 tools and network management scripts.